docs.lead_paragraph: Captain MCGOWAN has been held to bail at New-Orleans for "running quarantine," as the phrase goes; in other words, for refusing to anchor for ten days his vessel, the Crescent City, when, by his engagements with his employers, the public, and tile United States Government, he would be obliged to return to New-York in less than five.
